Let X be the random variable following Binomial distribution.Then,
\begin{align}
\pr{X = 1} &= p,
\\
\pr{X = k} &= \comb{n}{k}p^k\brak{1-p}^\brak{n-k}, \quad k = 0,\dots, n
\label{eq:exam44_1}
\end{align}
Here $p=\frac{1}{3}$ and $n=4$
Mean is given as
\begin{align}
\bar{X}=\sum_{k=0}^{n} k \pr{X=k}
\\
\bar{X}=\sum_{k=0}^{4} k \comb{4}{k}p^k\brak{1-p}^\brak{4-k}
\\
\bar{X}=\frac{1}{3}
\end{align}
